title: 409-E
statement: E. Dometime limit per test1 secondmemory limit per test256 megabytesinputstdinoutputstdoutInputThe input contains a single floating-point numberxwith exactly 6 decimal places (0 <x< 5).OutputOutput two integers separated by a single space. Each integer should be between 1 and 10, inclusive. If several solutions exist, output any of them. Solution will exist for all tests.ExamplesInput1.200000Output3 2Input2.572479Output10 3Input4.024922Output9 9

processed.result: Given a floating-point number $x$ between 0 and 5 (exclusive) with exactly 6 decimal places, find two integers between 1 and 10 inclusive.  The output should be the two integers separated by a space.  There will always be a solution.
Given a number between 0 and 5, find two whole numbers between 1 and 10 that represent a solution.
